<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4400] Rapidly opening and closing cores can lead to deadlock</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4400</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See the discussion at &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4196&quot; title=&quot;Untangle XML-specific nature of Config and Container classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4196&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4196&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Under ridiculous loads (i.e. every request causes a core to close and another one to open) Solr can lock up. This is &lt;em&gt;only&lt;/em&gt; a problem if you are using transient cores (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1028&quot; title=&quot;Automatic core loading unloading for multicore&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1028&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1028&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) with a limited cache size. Simply lazily loading cores that are NOT transient shouldn&apos;t have this problem, you need to be closing cores to get here.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
